What do you notice about it,

00:08:11.814 --> 00:08:13.749
about the language?
Yes.Student:

00:08:13.749 --> 00:08:14.837
They're using
"folks."Professor Amy

00:08:14.837 --> 00:08:15.659
Hungerford:
Yes.Student:

00:08:15.659 --> 00:08:16.868
He's addressing the
reader.Professor Amy

00:08:16.868 --> 00:08:19.143
Hungerford: Absolutely.
You would have to talk about

00:08:19.143 --> 00:08:21.790
that to get full credit for an
answer on this one.

00:08:21.790 --> 00:08:25.917
It's an address to the reader.
You'd need to talk about why he

00:08:25.917 --> 00:08:29.231
says that, so what would your
account be for why he says

00:08:29.231 --> 00:08:32.244
that?Student:
Because he's making a plea

00:08:32.244 --> 00:08:34.905
for his innocence,
and he's addressing people in

00:08:34.905 --> 00:08:37.192
this formal manner to try and
sort of reach them on a

00:08:37.192 --> 00:08:38.908
friendship
level…Professor

00:08:38.908 --> 00:08:40.360
Amy Hungerford:
Exactly.

00:08:40.360 --> 00:08:41.803
Student:
Yes, and then he just wants

00:08:41.803 --> 00:08:42.933
to sort of paint a picture of
his own

00:08:42.933 --> 00:08:44.660
morality.Professor Amy
Hungerford: Okay.

00:08:44.660 --> 00:08:47.200
Yes. Very good.
That's a very nice way of

00:08:47.200 --> 00:08:50.299
putting it, when you say he's
making a plea for his innocence.

00:08:50.299 --> 00:08:53.240
That is the whole context of
the novel.

00:08:53.240 --> 00:08:56.210
That's what sets up the novel;
that's the frame of the novel.

00:08:56.210 --> 00:08:59.610
And so, just by making that
observation, you've done an

00:08:59.610 --> 00:09:02.759
important thing for the passage
identifications,

00:09:02.759 --> 00:09:06.904
which is that you have drawn
its significance in the context

00:09:06.904 --> 00:09:10.139
of the larger novel,
the whole novel.

00:09:10.139 --> 00:09:17.546
What else might warrant your
notice here, what other bits of

00:09:17.546 --> 00:09:20.104
the language?
Yes.Student:

00:09:20.104 --> 00:09:21.773
The attention to
bodies.Professor Amy

00:09:21.773 --> 00:09:24.685
Hungerford: Yes.
What about that?Student:

00:09:24.685 --> 00:09:28.538
The opposition he sets up
