00:09:28.538 --> 00:09:30.601
Lolita's.
Professor Amy

00:09:30.601 --> 00:09:34.170
Hungerford: Absolutely,
yes, so that would be perfect,

00:09:34.170 --> 00:09:36.299
nice and economical.
What else?

00:09:36.299 --> 00:09:41.280
What else do you see there that
you could comment on?

00:09:44.520 --> 00:09:46.395
Yes.
Student:

00:09:46.395 --> 00:09:49.983
The way that he frames the
explanation like he's a

00:09:49.983 --> 00:09:53.299
hero.Professor Amy
Hungerford: Yes.

00:09:53.299 --> 00:09:55.869
Yeah, and what would you make
of that in an

00:09:55.869 --> 00:09:59.050
answer?Student:
Well, that as much as he's

00:09:59.050 --> 00:10:02.127
trying to prove his innocence,
he also really thinks he's

00:10:02.127 --> 00:10:04.277
actually doing the right thing
there.Professor Amy

00:10:04.277 --> 00:10:06.669
Hungerford: Yes.
